  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Distance du Khi-deux (χ²)\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.1 Justification du choix de la métrique\n",
    "\n",
    "En AFC, on utilise la **distance du Khi-deux** au lieu de la distance euclidienne pour deux raisons principales:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Indépendance des poids des colonnes**: Deux régions ne dépendent pas des \"poids\" respectifs des candidats. Si on regroupe deux candidats, les distances entre régions ne changent pas.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Propriété d'équivalence distributionnelle**: Si on regroupe deux modalités-lignes, les distances entre profils-colonne restent inchangées.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.2 Formule de la distance du Khi-deux\n",
    "\n",
    "Distance entre les lignes i et i':\n",
    "$$d_\\phi^2(L_i, L_{i'}) = \\sum_j \\frac{1}{f_{.j}} \\left(f_{j|i} - f_{j|i'}\\right)^2 = \\sum_j \\frac{1}{f_{.j}} \\left(\\frac{f_{ij}}{f_{i.}} - \\frac{f_{i'j}}{f_{i'.}}\\right)^2$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Distance entre les colonnes j et j':\n",
    "$$d_\\phi^2(C_j, C_{j'}) = \\sum_i \\frac{1}{f_{i.}} \\left(f_{i|j} - f_{i|j'}\\right)^2 = \\sum_i \\frac{1}{f_{i.}} \\left(\\frac{f_{ij}}{f_{.j}} - \\frac{f_{ij'}}{f_{.j'}}\\right)^2$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calcul des distances chi-deux entre régions\n",
    "def chi2_distance_rows(profile_rows, f_col):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calcule la matrice de distance chi-deux entre lignes\"\"\"\n",
    "    n_rows = profile_rows.shape[0]\n",
    "    distances = np.zeros((n_rows, n_rows))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(n_rows):\n",
    "        for i_prime in range(i, n_rows):\n",
    "            # Distance = sum_j (1/f_.j) * (f_j|i - f_j|i')^2\n",
    "            diff = profile_rows[i, :] - profile_rows[i_prime, :]\n",
    "            weighted_sq_diff = np.sum((diff ** 2) / f_col)\n",
    "            distances[i, i_prime] = weighted_sq_diff\n",
    "            distances[i_prime, i] = weighted_sq_diff\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return distances\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calcul des distances chi-deux entre candidats\n",
    "def chi2_distance_cols(profile_cols, f_row):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calcule la matrice de distance chi-deux entre colonnes\"\"\"\n",
    "    n_cols = profile_cols.shape[1]\n",
    "    distances = np.zeros((n_cols, n_cols))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for j in range(n_cols):\n",
    "        for j_prime in range(j, n_cols):\n",
    "            # Distance = sum_i (1/f_i.) * (f_i|j - f_i|j')^2\n",
    "            diff = profile_cols[:, j] - profile_cols[:, j_prime]\n",
    "            weighted_sq_diff = np.sum((diff ** 2) / f_row)\n",
    "            distances[j, j_prime] = weighted_sq_diff\n",
    "            distances[j_prime, j] = weighted_sq_diff\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return distances\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculer les distances\n",
    "dist_rows = chi2_distance_rows(profile_rows, f_col)\n",
    "dist_cols = chi2_distance_cols(profile_cols, f_row)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"ÉTAPE 4: Distance du Khi-deux\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher un exemple de calcul de distance\n",
    "print(\"\\nExemple: Distance chi-deux entre Alsace et Aquitaine\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "i_alsace = 0\n",
    "i_aquitaine = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"d²_φ(Alsace, Aquitaine) = {dist_rows[i_alsace, i_aquitaine]:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vérification manuelle pour les premiers candidats\n",
    "manual_calc = 0\n",
    "for j in range(min(3, len(df_raw.columns))):\n",
    "    term = ((profile_rows[i_alsace, j] - profile_rows[i_aquitaine, j]) ** 2) / f_col[j]\n",
    "    manual_calc += term\n",
    "    print(f\"  Candidat {j} ({df_raw.columns[j]}): ((${profile_rows[i_alsace, j]:.4f}$ - ${profile_rows[i_aquitaine, j]:.4f}$)² / ${f_col[j]:.4f}$) = ${term:.4f}$\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"  ... (+ autres candidats)\")\nprint(f\"  Somme = {dist_rows[i_alsace, i_aquitaine]:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher une sous-matrice de distances\n",
    "print(\"\\nMatrice de distances chi-deux entre régions (aperçu):\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_dist_rows = pd.DataFrame(dist_rows,\n",
    "                            index=df_raw.index,\n",
    "                            columns=df_raw.index)\n",
    "print(df_dist_rows.round(4).iloc[:5, :5])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Inertie totale\n",
    "\n",
    "### 7.1 Concept d'inertie en AFC\n",
    "\n",
    "L'inertie totale mesure le degré de liaison entre les deux variables (régions et candidats).\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\Phi^2 = \\sum_{i,j} f_{i.} f_{.j} t_{ij}^2 = \\sum_{i,j} \\frac{(f_{ij} - f_{i.}f_{.j})^2}{f_{i.}f_{.j}} = \\frac{\\chi^2}{N}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "où $t_{ij} = \\frac{f_{ij} - f_{i.}f_{.j}}{\\sqrt{f_{i.}f_{.j}}}$ sont les résidus standardisés.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Interprétation**:\n",
    "- Inertie = 0: indépendance totale\n",
    "- Inertie > 0: association entre les variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Résidus standardisés (taux de liaison)\n",
    "expected_freq = np.outer(f_row, f_col)  # f_{i.} * f_{.j}\n",
    "residuals = F - expected_freq\n",
    "standardized_residuals = residuals / np.sqrt(expected_freq)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Inertie totale\n",
    "inertia_total = np.sum(f_row[:, np.newaxis] * f_col[np.newaxis, :] * standardized_residuals ** 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Statistique chi-deux\n",
    "chi2_stat = N * inertia_total\n",
    "\n",
    "# Degrés de liberté et p-valeur\n",
    "df_chi2 = (F.shape[0] - 1) * (F.shape[1] - 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "from scipy.stats import chi2\n",
    "p_value = 1 - chi2.cdf(chi2_stat, df_chi2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"ÉTAPE 5: Inertie totale et test d'indépendance\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*100)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nΦ² (Inertie totale) = {inertia_total:.6f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"χ² = N × Φ² = {chi2_stat:,.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Degrés de liberté = {df_chi2}\")\n",
    "print(f\"p-valeur < 0.0001\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n→ La liaison entre régions et candidats est statistiquement significative\")\n",
    "print(f\"  (Rejet de l'hypothèse d'indépendance)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Afficher les résidus standardisés (taux de liaison) pour quelques cellules\n",
    "print(\"\\nRésidus standardisés (t_ij) - aperçu:\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_residuals = pd.DataFrame(standardized_residuals,\n",
    "                            index=df_raw.index,\n",
    "                            columns=df_raw.columns)\n",
    "print(df_residuals.round(3).iloc[:5, :5])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nInterprétation:\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Valeur positive: effectif observé > effectif attendu (attraction)\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Valeur négative: effectif observé < effectif attendu (répulsion)\")\n",
    "print(\"  - Valeur proche de 0: pas d'association particulière\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Matrice de transformation et SVD\n",
    "\n",
    "### 8.1 Matrice centrée réduite\n",
    "\n",
    "On applique une transformation à la matrice F pour extraire les directions de plus grande dispersion.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$Z_{ij} = \\frac{f_{ij} - f_{i.}f_{.j}}{\\sqrt{f_{i.}f_{.j}}} = \\sqrt{f_{i.}} \\cdot \\sqrt{f_{.j}} \\cdot \\frac{f_{ij} / (f_{i.} f_{.j}) - 1}{\\sqrt{f_{i.}} \\sqrt{f_{.j}}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "### 8.2 Décomposition en Valeurs Singulières (SVD)\n",
    "\n",
    "$$Z = U \\Lambda V^T$$\n",
    "\n",
    "où:\n",
    "- U: vecteurs singuliers pour les lignes\n",
    "- Λ: valeurs singulières (= √eigenvalues)\n",
    "- V: vecteurs singuliers pour les colonnes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Matrice de transformation centrée-réduite\n",
    "# Z_{ij} = (f_{ij} - f_i. * f_.j) / sqrt(f_i. * f_.j)\n",
    "Z = residuals / np.sqrt(expected_freq)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"ÉTAPE 6: Décomposition en Valeurs Singulières (SVD)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*100)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nMatrice Z (résidus standardisés normalisés):\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_Z = pd.DataFrame(Z,\n",
    "                   index=df_raw.index,\n",
    "                   columns=df_raw.columns)\n",
    "print(df_Z.round(4).iloc[:5, :5])\n",
    "\n",
    "# SVD: Z = U * Lambda * V^T\n",
    "U, singular_values, Vt = svd(Z, full_matrices=False)\n",
    "V = Vt.T\n",
    "\n",
    "# Valeurs propres (inertie par axe)\n",
    "eigenvalues = singular_values ** 2\n",
    "inertia_per_axis = eigenvalues / eigenvalues.sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nValeurs singulières et inerties par axe:\")\n",
    "print(\"-\" * 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_eigenvalues = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    'Axe': [f'Axe {i+1}' for i in range(len(singular_values))],\n",
    "    'Valeur singulière': singular_values,\n",
    "    'Valeur propre': eigenvalues,\n",
    "    'Inertie relative (%)': inertia_per_axis * 100,\n",
    "    'Inertie cumulée (%)': np.cumsum(inertia_per_axis) * 100\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df_eigenvalues.round(6).to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Déterminer le nombre d'axes à retenir\n",
    "cumulative_inertia = np.cumsum(inertia_per_axis)\n",
    "n_axes = np.argmax(cumulative_inertia >= 0.90) + 1  # 90% d'inertie\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n→ Nombre d'axes à retenir (pour 90% d'inertie): {n_axes}\")\n",
    "print(f\"→ Inertie cumulée sur les {n_axes} premiers axes: {cumulative_inertia[n_axes-1]*100:.2f}%\")"
   ]
